title: For Sale:  JM Browning 1919A4 Parts Kit (.308)
postcontent:
1919A4 parts kit! It's an Israeli build of the platfor, or perhaps an American made .308 that was shipped to Israel and then brought back as import as a parts kit.
 
I've had a few of you to ask about trade and consulted my dad about it and he's cool with it. (his kit, I wrote the sales copy because he's bad with computers) - We have an FFL dealer set up to receive shipment if any of you would like to go this route. He is looking for .308 battle rifles if any of you have an extra you'd be willing to part with in trade.
 
Right sideplate is destroyed per ATF but the rest of the parts are solid (I have a hard time imagining how anything John Moses Browning designed wouldn't be.)
 
Firing pin was still wrapped in paper when we found this kit and opened it up (it's nested in the block in the picture above). Got some belt links (not a lot but throwing them in for grins) and a service manual for it as well, but I need to dig these out of storage. In the event I can't find these I'll knock a little off the final price for the 1919 parts. Look over the picture carefully to make sure the lot has that rare part or crucial element you need to finish your replica build or make repairs to a legally owned functional weapon (if you're forunate enough to have one of these!).
Some of the surplus paint appears to have been buffed off while removing some gellied / lacquered (cosmolene-like?) substance, but the external metal is fine and the internal parts all seem to be in good shape.
 
Owing to their rarity, I don't know a great deal about belt fed weapons and I want to be honest about this up front. I'm happy to answer questions to the best of my ability and provide review material for any serious inquiries in the lot.
 
 
 
 
Shipping is available / preferred and included in the stated price. I can't find the option on Armslist to change this in the listing.
